< Review>
Absolutely the worst dining experience I've ever had in a restaurant. I ordered a very standard and popular Greek item called gyro.  What I got was a tortilla wrap with no tazike sauce and very little meat. I've eaten at this location before and the gyro was always good. Horrible!!!  No cucumbers or onions or tazike sauce. Two bites and I was done. I also asked for a A Greek salad on the side and got  lettuce with Italian dressing (no feta, olives or anything remotely related to a Greek salad).  I brought everything back up to the register and said this is horrible. The blonde  kid was wide-eyed and never offered an apology or money back. I walked out and will never return. I called the Huntington Beach Main Street restaurant and found out they sold this location to another owner six months ago  I spoke to James at the main street location and he said it wasn't their responsibility anymore despite having the same name. He said we have no control over what they serve. Wow!  I'm flabbergasted ! He said call Yasin, the owner, in the morning. The sense of urgency, care and pride is no longer a part of Coach's Mediterranean restaurant culture.<//Review>

I've been going to this office for about a year now. The front and back staff are always super friendly and nice. Especially the front office manager and the hygienist I see every 3 months. (Translated by Google) The fountain created by the Canadian artist Armand Vaillancourt officially bears the name "Quebec Libre!".
The idea for a fountain by Vaillancourt came from the imagination of Lawrence Halprin, a well-known landscape architect. In 1968 he announced that the fountain to be created by Vaillancourt would be considered one of America's "great works of civil art". After the installation of the artwork in 1971, however, the (expected) criticism did not fail to materialize.
Vaillancourt himself saw his work as a confrontational work that could serve as a magnet for protest and contradiction.
It should be noted that Interstate 480 thundered past here in 1971. The area has long since been redeveloped and the Bay Area has become a highly frequented area.
At first sight the fountain appears like a chaotically thrown pile of square concrete pipes. However, the chaos is not accidental, it was thought through by the artist to the place where it should be. Today it is provocatively free, the relieving newly built highway standing on pillars in the back. From this perspective, the fountain itself is ideally placed in the picture. Usually, however, you stand directly in front of the plant, which is up to 12 m high. From this perspective, the challenge is of course different, putting it in the sense of the construction, maybe confusing at the moment.
I personally like the cubic work from all perspectives.

(Original)

< review>
You won't find a more well versed, attentive, and well stocked nursery anywhere in the Santa Barbara area. These fine people run a store that's got a huge selection of plants and outdoor goodies, a huge selection of knowledge, and you can skip the big box shops of Home Depot and Osh to get a nursery experience that really delivers.

Got a problem with a plant? Bring in a clipping and they'll help you figure out what's wrong right on the spot. Also, free popcorn. Yeah.

Skip the Home Depot. Go here and support your local business because it's 100x better.<//review>

< text>
I dropped off my car several weeks ago to have Caliber fix the front bumper area of my car. I picked up my car on Friday the 13th around noon after dropping off the rental car and was initially impressed with the way the car looked.

However, upon driving the car, I noticed that my air conditioning was completely broken, which was curious because it was working fine before and after I got in an accident. I drove my car back to Caliber and told them about the problem, dropping my car off a second time. After sitting in the office for about an hour they told me that they couldn‚Äôt fix the problem until they ordered the right part. They received the part and called me on the following Tuesday to bring my car in for a third time. I had to borrow a car and have someone pick me up at the shop, which was rather inconvenient for both parties.

Caliber fixed the air conditioning system the next day, so I drove to the shop and picked it up again around 6:30pm. I turned the car on and the air conditioning worked perfectly ‚Äì the airbag system, however, didn‚Äôt. After troubleshooting the system, I dropped the car off at Caliber for a FOURTH time. Like the air conditioning system, this problem arose only AFTER Caliber worked on my car. Once again I had to borrow a car and get a ride. Eventually my car was finished correctly and I picked it up last Thursday, and so far there are no more problems.

Throughout this process I was in contact with the service advisor who repeatedly assured me that the car would be taken care off. I asked to speak with the manager several times to talk about these issues, but had no success. On Thursday she was too busy, and after being told several times that she would call, I waited on Friday (11/20) and Monday (11/23) and heard nothing back, even though I was told she would call me. To top it all off, the service adviser asked me to hide these issues from my insurance company and lie about it to them if they asked how the repairs went.

Then, when my insurance company came out to inspect the car, they found that Caliber did not align the hood properly with the front bumper, so I had to drop my car off for a FIFTH time.

Overall, all I got from Caliber was lip service. They told me they would fix my car, but each time I dropped the car off it had a new problem. I was told I could speak with the manager, but each time she was too busy or simply didn‚Äôt see it as a priority to call me back. < Text>
We bought a new air conditioning/heating unit last year for over $10,000 and are supposed to have a semi annual inspection of it to check to make sure everything is working. Their guy shows up with an attitude goes into our attic and claims we have a tear in the vents and it is not covered under our warranty. He said he say a mouse trap and when I asked if there was any droppings, he said no. We told him that the trap as been up there since we bought the home 5 years ago and that the picture of the damage was a clean tear, such with a knife. No bite marks at all. My husband and I told hem that the only people that have been in the attic is from Monarch, so either he did it today or the last guy that game 6 months ago did it. However, he is the only one that came with an attitude.

After telling us this he kept asking us if he wanted him to continue with his service and we kept saying do what you are supposed to do. He asked us two more times if we still wanted him to finish his service and we kept telling him yes. When he came down from the attic to show us the picture of the tear in the vent you can see that the tear was done with something sharp, like a knife. No rodent bites anywhere. We asked the service guy to call his supervisor, but he refused and instead held up his phone so I could have his number. I called him to let him know what is going on, of course I am upset, and the first thing he says is what does your contract say and to that I replied, isn't that your job to look up, for which he replies "CALM DOWN" which I wasn't yelling, cussing or even anything but being upset and he hangs up on me.

Now I have been waiting for days for supposedly the District Manager and then the General Manager to call me but with no success. I wait two days and call yet again and talk to another person that says she will look into this and make sure we didn't already have this tear. Amazing that when you tell a company that only they have ever been in your attic, they treat you like a criminal.

Please note, they are really nice for the initial sale and then they want more, more, more money for things you may not need and to fix things they will do to you.

My advise, hide a camera up there so you can film them.

Good luck!!
Marcia</Text>

I'm giving a low rating because of this company's blatant disrespect for me as a customer. The only reason my review is not lower is because of the amazing customer service I received from James Locke.

<text>DO NOT USE THEM FOR AIR CONDITIONING !!!!!

I am so disappointed with Monarch. Initially I was trying to contract my reliable service company Coleman of California, which serviced our unit bi-yearly, summer & winter but was connected to a toll number who had a Monarch rep. When I questioned if this was indeed Coleman of California, they tried to confuse me by saying yes we service for them, upon questioning them about the history of my unit, I quickly determined it was not the same company but later they finally admitted they bought out Coleman of California,. ( which translate we picked up their accounts).
I had been satisfied with the previous company so I had them send a tech since my ac was not cooling down. Long story short the first tech could barley make it from the van to my door without stopping for water, but made it to the roof, to tell us our capacitor went out to the blower, he replaced it charged a service & parts fee and checked the air for a few minutes, collected his check. After a very short time within 1 hour we noticed it was not cooling again. They sent our a different repair tech very late in the day, who tells us the first tech should of replaced the blower motor at the same time and would discount the cost of the capacitor and charge for the Blower Motor now. Since then I contacted the Manager Mark Dupree, who offered a free year service.
Unfortunately it has only been 2 months and the ac is NOT working, upon this visit, we're told the Fan Motor is fried and will cost $1000.00 to repair and they suggest a salesman to come over and review the cost of a new one $13,000.'s later, we say , " Thank you "  knowing they thought easy sale, dumb elderly people or whatever.
We have had the repair done by another A/C company referred by our reputable contractor whom we used for 30+ yrs. They were able to repair the problem informing us that, it is a old unit and will need more repairs but replacing will cost 1/3 of Monarch's price.  LESSON LEARNED...
